==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: muezzin
<hw>mu*ez"zin</hw> <pr>(m⟦usl⟧*⟦ecr⟧z"z⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Ar.]</ety> <def>A Muslim crier of the hour of prayer; the Moslem
official of a mosque who summons the faithful to prayer from a minaret
five times a day.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>mouezzin</asp>,
<asp>mueddin</asp>, <asp>muazzin</asp>, <asp>mu'adhdhin</asp>, and
<asp>muwazzin</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

